<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[In replying, quote the following
                                    initial letter M.]</seg></opener>
                            <head><persName type="from">The Admiralty</persName> to <persName type="to">Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Admiralty,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-12"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 12, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen:</hi> I have received and laid before
                                my lords commissioners of the admiralty your letter of the 7th
                                instant, calling attention to the present condition of the two steam
                                vessels, El Tousson and El Monnassir, and as to the preservation of
                                the property on board from injury, &amp;c.</p>
                            <p>I am, gentlemen, your most obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>C. PAGET.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Messrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Laird</hi> &amp; Co., <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>